Sentencas: As the first part of a two paper series, we present a two-dimensional impedance model of a working solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) to study the effect of contact degradation on the impedance spectrum for the purpose of non-invasive diagnosis.
Titulo: Short-stack modeling of degradation in solid oxide fuel cells - Part I. Contact degradation

Sentencas: The two dimensional modeled geometry includes the ribbed interconnect, and is adequate to represent co- and counter-flow configurations.
Titulo: Short-stack modeling of degradation in solid oxide fuel cells - Part I. Contact degradation

Sentencas: Simulated degradation modes include: cathode delamination, interconnect oxidation, and interconnect-cathode detachment.
Titulo: Short-stack modeling of degradation in solid oxide fuel cells - Part I. Contact degradation

Sentencas: The simulations show differences in the way each degradation mode impacts the impedance spectrum shape, suggesting that identification is possible.
Titulo: Short-stack modeling of degradation in solid oxide fuel cells - Part I. Contact degradation

Sentencas: In Part II, we present a sensitivity analysis of the results to input parameter variability that reveals strengths and limitations of the method, as well as describing possible interactions between input parameters and concurrent degradation modes.
Titulo: Short-stack modeling of degradation in solid oxide fuel cells - Part I. Contact degradation
